China and nine Caribbean countries will hold a foreign ministers' meeting via video link on Friday, Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesperson Wang Wenbin announced on Thursday. Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi and Dominican Prime Minister Roosevelt Skerrit will co-host the meeting, which will be attended by all nine of the Caribbean countries that have established diplomatic ties with China, the spokesperson said at a regular press briefing. The parties involved will exchange views on the relationship between China and the Caribbean region and issues of common concern, he said. (Cover: File photo of Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi. /Xinhua)